        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 7 at 6:24PM CDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 624 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 4 miles northeast of Bird City, or 16 miles east of St.
Francis, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
McDonald around 640 PM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
